  "semantic_summary": "This table contains detailed records of Olympic medalists, including their Wikidata IDs, Wikipedia links, names, medals won, and associated delegations. It captures the country each medal is attributed to, with various country codes (ISO2, ISO3, IOC), and links to Wikidata for countries and delegations. The table records the athlete's date and place of birth, with both textual and Wikidata references, as well as geographic coordinates (latitude and longitude). It includes information about the athlete's gender (with Wikidata ID and label), the event in which the medal was won (with Wikidata ID, Wikipedia link, and event name), and the broader event or sport context. There are also fields for NUTS regional codes and names (NUTS0, NUTS1, NUTS2, NUTS3), as well as population and GDP data for NUTS2 and NUTS3 regions, which are primarily relevant for European athletes. This structure supports complex queries about medalists, their demographics, the events they participated in, and the geographic and economic context of their origins.",
